<P N="38"><PB N="109" REF="015100_0108_0F95D2EBAAACBE60">38. Take tops of common wormwood two ounces, roots of calamus aromaticus, gentian, imperatory, of each one ounce, bay berries one ounce and a half, juniper berries three ounces, wild carrot feed one ounce. Cut, brui&s;e, mix. Infu&s;e warm in a clo&s;e va&s;e, in, either good wine of mead, eight pounds, for twenty four hours.</P>
