<P>EXTRACTS FROM THE MARINE PRACTICE OF PHYSIC AND SURGERY.</P>
<P>WITH SOME BRIEF DIRECTIONS TO BE OBSERVED BY SEA-SURGEONS IN ENGAGEMENTS, &amp;c.</P>
<P>BY WILLIAM NORTHCOTE, SURGEON, MANY YEARS IN THE SEA-SERVICE.</P>
<P>Including, The NATURE and TREATMENT, of GUN-SHOT WOUNDS.</P>
<P>BY JOHN RANBY, E&s;quire; SURGEON GENERAL TO THE BRITISH ARMY.</P>
<P>PHILADELPHIA: Printed, and Sold, by R. BELL, in Third-Street. MDCCLXXVI.</P>
</DIV1>
</FRONT>
